    <string name="lesson_pawn_title">Pawn</string>
    <string name="lesson_pawn_intro">The pawn is the most humble piece, but it can become the most powerful if it reaches the end of the board.</string>
    <string name="lesson_pawn_body">Here you will learn how the pawn moves, how it captures, what the initial double step is, and how promotion works. You will also see practical video examples.</string>

    <string name="lesson_bishop_title">Bishop</string>
    <string name="lesson_bishop_intro">The bishop controls the diagonals and works best in pairs.</string>
    <string name="lesson_bishop_body">Learn the bishops diagonal movement, its strengths in open positions, and how to coordinate it with other pieces.</string>

    <string name="lesson_knight_title">Knight</string>
    <string name="lesson_knight_intro">The knight moves in an L-shape and can jump over other pieces.</string>
    <string name="lesson_knight_body">Discover typical jumping patterns, strong squares for the knight, and tactics like the fork.</string>

    <string name="lesson_rook_title">Rook</string>
    <string name="lesson_rook_intro">The rook is very powerful on open files and ranks.</string>
    <string name="lesson_rook_body">You will see how to activate your rooks, use open files, and coordinate doubled rooks.</string>

    <string name="lesson_queen_title">Queen</string>
    <string name="lesson_queen_intro">The queen combines the power of the rook and the bishop.</string>
    <string name="lesson_queen_body">Learn how to use the queen without overexposing it and how to finish decisive attacks.</string>

    <string name="lesson_king_title">King</string>
    <string name="lesson_king_intro">The king is the most important piece: if it is checkmated, the game is over.</string>
    <string name="lesson_king_body">You will see concepts such as castling, king safety, and activating the king in endgames.</string>

    <string name="lesson_moves_title">Basic moves</string>
    <string name="lesson_moves_intro">Before attacking, you must know how each piece moves.</string>
    <string name="lesson_moves_body">General review of the moves of all pieces, with visual examples and typical situations.</string>

    <string name="lesson_rules_title">Basic rules</string>
    <string name="lesson_rules_intro">Learn the essential rules of chess.</string>
    <string name="lesson_rules_body">Explanation of check, checkmate, draw, stalemate, castling, en passant capture, and other basic rules.</string>

